The paper discusses the development of agent teams for complex, dynamic multi-agent domains, which is a key area of research in artificial intelligence (AI). Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also focuses on teamwork and coordination among agents, which falls under the sub-category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The paper also discusses the application of these agent teams in areas such as education, training, and entertainment, which are related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also mentions the use of decision-theoretic communication, which is related to control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper presents empirical results, which suggests the use of machine learning (cs.LG) techniques.
